===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|𤔔|乙|alt2=乚|tr1=*[r]ˁo[n]-s|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}}. The left-side component {{zh-m|*𤔔}} is itself ideogrammatic, depicting the effort to comb a tangle of threads, hence the semantic link to order and disorder.

===Etymology===
Area word of {{cog|aav}} origin. Compare {{cog|km|ប្រួល||changing; unstable}} < {{cog|km|រួល||to cook; to grill}}, and also {{cog|km|កំរោល||to go berserk; to become excited}} < {{cog|km|រោល||to burn; to roast}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). {{cog|my|ရုန်း||to struggle, to warp, to cause chaos}} and {{cog|bo|ཁྲལ་ཁྲུལ||fragments; scattered}} are {{cog|aav}} loans. Compare also {{cog|vi|lộn||to [[turn]] the [[inside]] [[out]], [[upside]] [[down]], to [[reverse]], to [[return]], etc.}} and {{m|vi|trộn||to mix, to blend}}.

